FBIS4-8221 "dreeu070_b_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-070 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 BULGARIA Hungarian Vessels Allowed To Leave Vidin Hungarian Vessels Allowed To Leave Vidin AU1204102594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0800 GMT 12 Apr 94 AU1204102594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Report by Totka Ninova] [Text] The two Hungarian tugs Vac and Egzsenek have just set sail from the Vidin bank of the Danube. The two vessels were detained by representatives of the Western European Union, the Bulgarian State Navigation Inspectorate, and Vidin customs. The vessels had to stay there for four days so that they could be provided with the necessary UN permits allowing them to sail to Hungary. The two vessels are towing five barges loaded with 991 tonnes of phosphate.
